For each of the {= service_line =} steel-service lines listed below, identify {= provider_service =}+ Lower Mainland-facing provider/service pairs and cover each of the {= evidence_facet =} evidence facets for every pair through each of the {= source_role =} source roles listed below, with {= url =}+ public URL for each source role. Each URL should independently substantiate the provider identity, local market tie, selected service line, submitted source role, and facet-specific public finding.

The useful public objects are provider identity, local role, steel-service scope, customer access path, and concrete logistics or terms posture. Supplier ranking, installed-cost comparison, contractor recommendation, quote solicitation, outreach, contact enrichment, lead scoring, review sentiment, renovation advice, engineering/design advice, and product/project suitability conclusions are out of scope.

Steel-service lines:
- `structural_beam_supply_or_processing`: steel service centers, metal suppliers, warehouses, stores, or processors publicly offering structural steel shapes or processing, such as beams, HSS/tube, channel/angle, plate, cutting, pickup, or delivery.
- `structural_steel_fabrication_or_installation`: fabricators, installers, erectors, or contractors publicly offering structural steel packages, beams, columns, frames, stairs, seismic steel, or comparable structural steel fabrication / installation work.
- `steel_stud_or_light_gauge_framing`: contractors or services publicly offering steel stud, light-gauge steel, metal-stud, wall, ceiling, or related framing work.
- `misc_metal_sheet_metal_or_custom_steel_fabrication`: custom steel, miscellaneous metals, sheet metal, architectural/ornamental metal, welding, or custom fabrication services where the page visibly presents a steel or metal fabrication scope.

Evidence facets:
- `local_service_role`: evidence that the provider/service is Lower Mainland-facing and what public role the page supports, such as branch/store, shop, supplier, fabricator, installer, erector, contractor, service-area provider, directory-listed specialty, or trade/listing context.
- `steel_scope`: evidence of the submitted steel product or service scope for the selected service line.
- `commercial_access_path`: source-stated customer access or transaction path, such as posted purchasing, add-to-cart, request-quote, free-estimate, branch ordering, budgetary quote, provider-specific marketplace/order profile, or comparable public access framing tied to the provider/service.
- `logistics_or_terms_detail`: source-stated logistics, timing, or terms detail, such as delivery, pickup, cut-to-size, no minimum order, lead time, quote turnaround, same-day/fast-service preparation, pricing/availability varying by store, stock-length framing, staged installation process, or comparable operational term tied to the provider/service.

Source roles:
- `provider_controlled`: a provider-owned, provider-operated, branch/location, chain-owned, verified provider social, or provider-authored page where the provider itself controls or visibly authors the source surface.
- `independent_operational_trace`: a public source not controlled by the provider that independently traces the provider/service through provider-specific operational or trade substance, such as a project profile, permit/registry record, trade association or contractor-network profile, supplier/marketplace profile, public contract or inspection trace, supplier-network page, or focused trade/editorial article.

`provider` should be a real public commercial/trade entity, branch/location, or named contractor/service provider. Providers or branches can appear in more than one service line only when each provider/service-line pairing is publicly supported. For the two commercial facets, residential/commercial/industrial audience or project-scope labels can contextualize a concrete access, logistics, timing, or terms finding, but are not enough by themselves. Standards, certification, code, seismic, permit, or engineering language counts only as a public source claim, not as a conclusion that work or products are compliant, safe, approved, suitable, legally adequate, or appropriate for a project. Sources should be public, usable pages rather than generic cost guides, job postings, project tenders, social/review-sentiment pages, private RFQ portals, search result pages, contact-only lead forms, or lead-generation surfaces. Generic business directories, scraped contact pages, and map-style listings qualify only when they carry provider-specific operational or trade substance beyond name, address, phone, hours, ratings, map pin, broad category, or generic service-area text.

Requirements:
- The page must clearly identify the named provider, branch/location, or contractor/service provider.
- The page must credibly tie the provider/service to the Lower Mainland, Metro Vancouver, Vancouver, Surrey, North Vancouver, West Vancouver, Fraser Valley, or another clearly in-scope BC local service/store/branch/service-area context.
- The page must bind the provider to the submitted service line.
- The page should make the submitted source role visible: for `provider_controlled`, through provider-owned domain, branch/location page, official chain page, verified provider social channel, provider-authored article, or comparable provider-control/authorship signals; for `independent_operational_trace`, through independent project, permit, registry, trade-association, contractor-network, supplier-network, marketplace, public contract, inspection, or focused trade/editorial framing that names the provider/service and carries provider-specific operational or trade substance beyond a thin contact listing.
- The page should make its facet-appropriate source framing visible: for `local_service_role`, local branch/service-area, official-provider, independent operational/trade, or comparable local-role framing; for `steel_scope`, product/category/service/project framing tied to the selected steel-service line; for `commercial_access_path`, product/service, ordering, quote/free-estimate, branch-ordering, provider-specific marketplace/supplier profile, or comparable public access-path framing; for `logistics_or_terms_detail`, product/service, location, ordering, process, FAQ, quote, delivery, installation, or comparable page framing that can actually state an operational term.
- The page should expose a focused public finding for the selected evidence facet: for `local_service_role`, the local role/service-area/branch or public role signal; for `steel_scope`, the steel product/service detail; for `commercial_access_path`, a source-stated purchase, quote, estimate, ordering, branch access, supplier/marketplace access path, or comparable customer-access path that is more than a generic phone/address/contact listing; for `logistics_or_terms_detail`, a source-stated delivery/pickup, timing/lead-time, minimum-order, cut-to-size, quote-turnaround, pricing/availability, stock-length, staged installation, or comparable concrete logistics / terms detail that is more than ordinary business hours or contact metadata.
